<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870806-0030 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:</HL><DD> 08/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AVLTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Avalon Corp. said a unit purchased oil and natural gas producing properties from closely held JN Oil andamp; Gas Inc., Billings, Mont. Terms weren't disclosed.    Avalon, a New York-based energy and real estate concern, said the properties are in the Williston Basin in Montana and in North Dakota; the Sweetgrass Arch in Montana; and the Denver-Julesberg Basin in Colorado. They have estimated reserves of 1.4 million barrels of oil and 3.3 billion cubic feet of gas. </TEXT></DOC>